    "body": "Potential fix for https://github.com/spack/spack/issues/7356\r\n\r\nIt appears that `OperatingSystem` should be careful to format the provided name, since it looks like that name may contain a `-` (which is used by `ArchSpec` to delineate between platform, os, and target), for example if the `distname` reported by `external.distro.linux_distribution` (as used in `LinuxDistro`) contains a `-` (I should say I'm not 100% sure if `external.distro.linux_distribution` allows `-` but a cursory glance suggests it may be possible).",
